Our Song (Savich/Wanchic)

[A-] [G] [A-]

I had a dream you had a nightmare, Something held you down,

[G]

crying out it swallowed up the sound, but I was there beside you a
whisper in the dark

[C] [G]

A breath to coax a flame from your spark, When fire floods a room,
shadows harden too

[C] [G]

Stark lines are drawn dividing me from you, So let’s not start too
bright

[A-] [G] [A-]

And grow our love by heat of twilight

[G] [C]

