Roll it away (Savich)

[F#] [G#-]

I’ve eaten gloom

[C#] [B] [F#]

Goodbyes said by thousands before noon

It came on quick, and sickly strong

Like shooting Turkey after dad was gone

Roll it away, roll it away

You’re more than just the sum of tunes you play

The simple truth: there’s more to say

But when it’s time the next line finds a page

I was scared to swim

The water up the door was leaking in

I thought to call, but didn’t cave

Though the urge came on me wave on wave

Roll it away, roll it away

Fly, my little yearnings, to your graves

Then to the blue, deep breath alive

I will strip the skin off of my scales and dive

I can’t feel your pain

But I’ve spun and worn and wove the cloth of rain

A shiver loosed betrays the bet

I will whet the blade to lose the best thing yet

F# F7 A#-#5 A#-#5/F

I need a bridge

[Ddim] [Fdim7] [D#-]

A crutch to clutch through the worst of it

[B] [C#] [F#] [C#/F] [D#-]

I’m so glad you called, I was really in a fit

[B] [C#] [D#-]

A hit of warm to curb the loneliness

[B] [C#] [F#]

“Better than I’d hoped, worse than I’d wish”

Roll it away, roll it away

May the star of your tomorrow shine today

Be the blue in growing green

May you dance along the summer’s edge of dream

Still feels like home (Savich)

[D#] [A#]

I cut my hand on a carpet knife

[G#] [D#] [A#]

Tearing out the mold-dark night

Nothing goes quite as wrong

As when you truly try

After years and years and years of just getting by

Letting the summer wind blow the rain in

And the curtains drip on the floor

With every storm a little more was breaking

Now I can’t afford replacing the warped boards: the house is getting old

Broke my crown soaking up storm light

Held my breath to arrest the slide

Julie wrote it down, said: “don’t forget,

Dead head to keep on growing,

Or learn to stomach your regrets

Cause the summer wind’s gonna blow the rain in

‘Til the curtains drip on the floor

With every storm you’ll find a little more is breaking

‘Til you can’t afford replacing the warped boards and curse getting old”

[D#] [C#]

But other words blow in on the same warm wind

[F#] [G#]

Filling cracks with honey dripping from the comb

[C#] [F-] [F#] [G#]

It still feels like home

[C#] [F-] [F#] [G#]

Can’t help it, it feels like home

[C#] [G#]

Cut my hand on a carpet knife

[F#] [C#] [G#]

Held my breath to arrest the slide

[C#] [G#]

It feels so wrong in the mold-dark night

[F#] [G#]

Then you peeled those sodden curtains from my eyes

Awoke to golden light

Tell the family I’m doing alright

I cut my hand

