Caroline (Savich)

C#- (riff)

At first you loved a man, oh you loved him like a brother

You swore there’d be no other, oh you’d wait home by the door

You drove him like a hailstone every thunder-shrouded evening

A moon-burnt husk is all you take me for

Oh, oh, oh, oh, Caroline, Carolina

Ash on treaded boots beats out a tattoo on the floor

Oh, oh, oh, oh, Caroline, Carolina

There’s a dark wolf a’ dancin’ ‘round your door

You pulled a feather from his wings, set fire to the rachis

The tindered flame burnt soft and green, but seethed in the abyss

Lips to stone, tongue to bone, you plucked out all the others

A flightless bird is all you take me for

